Supported File Formats in Data Cloud

Data Cloud supports various files and compression formats for your data stream sources.

Supported File Types
IMPORTANT We recommend you refer Data Cloud Limits and Guidelines to know the applicable file limitations.

Data Cloud supports these file formats:

Delimited text files such as CSV files.
Parquet files when data is ingested from Amazon S3, Google Cloud Storage, Microsoft Azure Storage.
NOTE You must use ASCII characters in text fields such as file name, wildcard, directory name, or formula syntax editor. UTF-8 sometimes contains non-ASCII characters that aren’t guaranteed to work properly. Also, don't use :(colon) and ' (single quote) in file names and formulas.
Supported Delimiters

Data Cloud supports these content delimiters for text files:

, (comma)
\t (tab)
| (pipe)
; (semicolon)
^ (caret)
¦ (broken pipe)
\u0001
NOTE Data Cloud automatically evaluates the ingested files and determines the delimiter. We recommend using double quotes around values in a file to ensure the system detects the correct file delimiter.
Supported File Compression Formats

Data Cloud supports these compression formats for CSV files:

GZ
ZIP

Data Cloud supports these compression formats for the data in the Parquet files:

GZ
ZIP
NONE
SNAPPY
ZSTD
Ingestion of Parquet Files

Data Cloud supports these parquet data types and they’re converted to the corresponding Data Cloud data types. If a parquet file contains a data type that's not supported in Data Cloud, the column is ignored and not ingested. You can view the unsupported fields when configuring the data stream in the New Data Stream page. You can also see the unsupported data types in the New Source Fields page when adding a source field. To ingest an unsupported data type. convert it to a Data Cloud supported datatype in the source parquet file.

PARQUET DATA TYPE	DATA CLOUD DATA TYPE
STRING	Text
ENUM
UUID
BOOLEAN*	Boolean
DATE	Date
TIMESTAMP	Datetime
INT96*
DECIMAL with 38 precision, 18 scale	Number
DOUBLE*
FLOAT
INT
INT32*
INT64*
NOTE * Indicates a primitive data type in Parquet files.

Data Cloud supports the following encoding formats for parquet files:

Run-length encoding (RLE) Dictionary
Plain Dictionary
